Hawks spokesperson Captain Philani Nkwalase says their PetroSA investigation is still in its early stages. JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks in the Western Cape have confirmed they are investigating allegations of fraud and corruption at the state petrochemical producer, PetroSA. It’s understood several officials are accused of procurement corruption as well as nepotism and bribery. Hawks spokesperson Captain Philani Nkwalase says their PetroSA investigation is still in its early stages. “There’s an investigation that’s currently ongoing and the charges relate to fraud and corruption.” Fin24 is reporting the complaint was lodged by a community member at a police station in Mossel Bay. The suspects allegedly fraudulently claimed grants from the sector’s training authority by submitting claims for ghost pupils. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)